    "description": "<ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Play Through <strong><u>12 Unique Scenarios</u></strong> and <strong><u>Over 20 Quick Play Stages</u></strong><br></li><li>Choose From <strong><u>6 Different Companies</u></strong>, Each with Their Own Strengths and Weaknesses<br></li><li>Go <strong><u>Bird Watching</u></strong> in your Free Time and Spot Them All</li></ul><br>To be a successful CEO in Frack the World, you must manage various systems, including oil production, finances, environmental impact, and public perception. The game is a lite land management sort of puzzle game, with matches lasting 10 minutes on average. The gameplay has two fronts: the Underground, where you strategically extend pipes to extract oil while overcoming obstacles; and the Surface, where you build and manage facilities while dealing with external challenges like protests and pollution.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2256900/extras/32d9f079840df4ccc3aa99914fd06ceb.webp?t=1684704767\" width=768 height=10 /></span><br><br>When things are running smoothly, you get to chill for a minute and distract yourself with some casual <strong>CEO </strong>things.<br><br><i>Try finding and viewing all of the high-fidelity birds</i> in the sky and go read all about these majestic birds thanks to facts found in a bird book from a thrift store and sometimes Wikipedia! Lose yourself in <strong>Bird Mode</strong>! All the joys of bird watching with none of the fracking!<br><br><i>Hire staff and have them rattle off tons of info</i> to you in the news scroll. Or keep your eye out for great news stories about how wonderful your business is and how fracking is actually super beneficial to the planet.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2256900/extras/32d9f079840df4ccc3aa99914fd06ceb.webp?t=1684704767\" width=768 height=10 /></span><br><br>While every game may eventually end with environmental destruction, at least you can make <strong>TONS</strong> of money in the meantime. Because, honestly, every match of real life will end with planetary destruction too. But at least in this game you are the <strong>CEO</strong>!",
